  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Buy</h2>

  <p>
    For most home setups, buy sturdy bottom-watering trays that match your seed-starting inserts and provide enough depth for even water absorption. Avoid very thin trays and prioritize durability if you plan to reuse them each season.
  </p>

  <p>
    Choose slightly deeper trays if your seedlings will stay indoors longer or if you want more consistent watering with less effort. In most cases, a simple, well-fitting tray system works better than a complicated integrated setup.
  </p>

